## looping or iterative statements
there are 3 statements
1.while loop :*first it checks the confition if the condition is true it goes through the body of the statement,otherwise it exit and donot print anything
syntax : while(conndition)
        {


       }
example : #include<stdio.hh>
          void main()
          {
               int n,i;
               printf("enter the upper limit);
               scanf("%d",&n);
               i = 2;
               while(i<= n)
               {
                printf("%d\t",i);
               i = i+2
}
2.for loop : *first it will asssigns or initialize a value and go to the condition if it is true it goes to the body and increment or decrement and again the check the  confition.
syntax : for(intialize;condition;increment/decrement)
          {
       }
example :{
           int n,i;
          printf("enter upper limit");
          scanf("%d",&n);
          for(i = 2;i<=n;i=i+2)
          printf("%d\t",i);
}
3.do-while loop: *first it will check  the while condition and goes through the do to body
syntax: do{



          }while(condition)
       }
example : {
int n,i;;
printf("enter upper limit");
scanf("%d",&n);
i = 2;
do{
printf("%d\t",i);
i = i+2;
}while(i<=n);
}
            
